1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,962
[reporter] <i>Presidential Chief of Staff</i>
<i>Ahmad Mustapha was killed.</i>

2
00:00:04,045 --> 00:00:05,839
<i>According to the initial report,</i>

3
00:00:05,922 --> 00:00:09,050
<i>his vehicle was blown up</i>
<i>by drone missiles.</i>

4
00:00:09,134 --> 00:00:12,053
- [reporter] <i>Who was behind it?</i>
- <i>You know who you are.</i>

5
00:00:12,137 --> 00:00:13,179
<i>You'd better hide</i>

6
00:00:13,263 --> 00:00:16,307
because we won't stop
until you're rotting in prison.

7
00:00:16,391 --> 00:00:18,810
[Manuel] <i>I strongly suspect Allan Espina.</i>

8
00:00:18,893 --> 00:00:22,522
<i>Mustapha was the one</i>
<i>who put him in the NLEA and the SID!</i>

9
00:00:22,605 --> 00:00:23,940
Find out what he knows.

10
00:00:24,023 --> 00:00:27,110
[Datu Rahman] <i>I tried</i>
<i>to stop the explosion. But I failed.</i>

11
00:00:27,193 --> 00:00:29,195
<i>That's how I found your brother, Jalil.</i>

12
00:00:29,279 --> 00:00:31,531
<i>He was the son of my friend Victor.</i>

13
00:00:31,614 --> 00:00:33,908
[Jamilah]
<i>Are you Doctor Teresa's missing son?</i>

14
00:00:33,992 --> 00:00:36,286
[Madam President]
<i>He served this country with honor</i>

15
00:00:36,369 --> 00:00:37,579
<i>until his very last breath.</i>

16
00:00:37,662 --> 00:00:40,498
So whoever's behind this crime,

17
00:00:40,582 --> 00:00:43,334
you will be found,
and justice will be served.

18
00:00:43,418 --> 00:00:45,754
I will get to the bottom of this.

19
00:00:45,837 --> 00:00:47,630
You can count on me, Madam President.

20
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:49,799
[Marcus]
<i>We need to bring General Carillo down.</i>

21
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:51,885
[Jalil] <i>Let's go after his accomplices.</i>

22
00:00:51,968 --> 00:00:53,803
General Carillo is too good.

23
00:00:53,887 --> 00:00:55,138
[Marcus] <i>When it comes to his henchmen,</i>

24
00:00:55,221 --> 00:00:56,139
<i>we may be able to get something.</i>

25
00:00:56,222 --> 00:00:57,474
<i>Domingo's one of them too?</i>

26
00:00:58,433 --> 00:01:00,185
- [Azuelo] <i>Domingo.</i>
- [Felix] <i>What's going on?</i>

27
00:01:00,268 --> 00:01:01,811
- [Felix] <i>What are you doing here?</i>
- [Azuelo] <i>Nothing.</i>

28
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:03,730
[Azuelo]
<i>We were just talking about something.</i>

29
00:01:04,564 --> 00:01:06,900
[Usman] <i>What will happen to you now?</i>
<i>Sir Mustapha is gone.</i>

30
00:01:06,983 --> 00:01:07,901
- [Usman] <i>They can--</i>
- [Jalil] <i>I'll be fine.</i>

31
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:09,819
Why don't you just tell Marcus?

32
00:01:09,903 --> 00:01:12,697
If my identity gets revealed,
only I should go down for it.

33
00:01:12,781 --> 00:01:14,282
<i>He can't get dragged in it.</i>

34
00:01:18,369 --> 00:01:20,163
[theme music playing]

35
00:01:38,014 --> 00:01:40,266
I can't believe Sir Mustapha's gone.

36
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:42,310
Many were hoping he could do something

37
00:01:42,393 --> 00:01:44,354
to fix the mess happening in our country.

38
00:01:44,437 --> 00:01:45,563
I know.

39
00:01:46,564 --> 00:01:48,817
What happened to him was too much.
They bombed his car.

40
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:50,777
They made sure he won't survive.

41
00:01:52,737 --> 00:01:54,948
Still, let's not lose hope.

42
00:01:57,158 --> 00:01:59,661
Oh. What happened to you?

43
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:03,039
It's still so early,
but it looks like a battalion beat you up.

44
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:05,458
Well, there's a lot of violence around.

45
00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:07,502
It's just trouble after trouble.

46
00:02:07,585 --> 00:02:11,548
Everyone's fighting,
everyone's killing each other,

47
00:02:11,631 --> 00:02:13,049
instead of loving each other?

48
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:15,677
Well, criminals are no longer afraid.

49
00:02:17,178 --> 00:02:18,388
Come on.

50
00:02:18,471 --> 00:02:20,223
[pensive music playing]

51
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:29,732
Based on our previous assessment,

52
00:02:29,816 --> 00:02:31,442
everything happened
according to your plan, General.

53
00:02:32,026 --> 00:02:33,069
[Manuel chuckling]

54
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:35,321
And you're right on schedule, General.

55
00:02:35,905 --> 00:02:36,823
Good.

56
00:02:37,949 --> 00:02:39,242
Hm.

57
00:02:39,826 --> 00:02:44,414
However, there's a snake in our grass.

58
00:02:47,375 --> 00:02:48,668
[chuckles]

59
00:02:48,751 --> 00:02:52,797
We need to purge the traitor…

60
00:02:53,506 --> 00:02:55,425
in our own ranks.

61
00:02:55,925 --> 00:02:58,428
[ominous music playing]

62
00:03:09,814 --> 00:03:12,734
[Manuel] <i>Dante, what did you do?</i>

63
00:03:13,610 --> 00:03:17,989
<i>You were the only one</i>
<i>who could tell Lara the truth.</i>

64
00:03:19,324 --> 00:03:23,786
<i>I lost my daughter because of you!</i>

65
00:03:25,079 --> 00:03:27,081
<i>Three more men are dead</i>

66
00:03:27,165 --> 00:03:30,209
<i>after being shot by men on a motorcycle.</i>

67
00:03:30,293 --> 00:03:33,087
<i>This is in addition</i>
<i>to the increasing number</i>

68
00:03:33,171 --> 00:03:35,048
<i>of cases of violence in the country.</i>

69
00:03:35,131 --> 00:03:38,301
[tense music playing]

70
00:03:42,263 --> 00:03:44,724
Did Manuel send you to kill me?

71
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:48,978
[gunshots]

72
00:03:49,062 --> 00:03:50,521
[bodies thud]

73
00:03:50,605 --> 00:03:53,399
[tense music continues]

74
00:03:59,405 --> 00:04:00,865
General Guerzon…

75
00:04:04,702 --> 00:04:05,828
Let's go.

76
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:16,589
This looks delicious!

77
00:04:16,673 --> 00:04:17,924
[laughs]

78
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:20,760
[tense music continues]

79
00:04:24,055 --> 00:04:26,683
Ouch! You bastard!
You think you're all that?

80
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:27,850
- [man 1] Hey, what's your problem?
- [man 2] You bumped into me!

81
00:04:28,518 --> 00:04:30,144
- Stop!
- [blows landing]

82
00:04:30,228 --> 00:04:32,230
- [man] He has a gun!
- [gunshots]

83
00:04:32,313 --> 00:04:33,982
[people screaming]

84
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:41,489
<i>The alarming increase in cases</i>

85
00:04:41,572 --> 00:04:43,866
<i>of gun-related violence</i>
<i>in the country continues.</i>

86
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:48,079
<i>Experts say that the public</i>
<i>is losing their fear and respect</i>

87
00:04:48,162 --> 00:04:50,540
<i>for the police force and the government.</i>

88
00:04:50,623 --> 00:04:52,542
<i>This is allegedly a result</i>
<i>of a lack of confidence</i>

89
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:55,336
<i>in their abilities to resolve</i>

90
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:57,714
<i>the continued proliferation</i>
<i>of illegal weapons.</i>

91
00:04:57,797 --> 00:04:58,798
[gunshots]

92
00:04:59,757 --> 00:05:01,217
<i>Since no one has been held accountable</i>

93
00:05:01,301 --> 00:05:03,011
<i>for the murder</i>
<i>of the Presidential Chief of Staff</i>

94
00:05:03,094 --> 00:05:04,512
<i>Ahmad Mustapha,</i>

95
00:05:04,595 --> 00:05:08,182
<i>the public thinks that even</i>
<i>the more powerful officials</i>

96
00:05:08,266 --> 00:05:12,562
<i>in the government</i>
<i>cannot protect themselves.</i>

97
00:05:12,645 --> 00:05:13,813
Worthless!

98
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:17,066
This government is useless!

99
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:20,945
You can't even count on the police!

100
00:05:21,029 --> 00:05:23,740
Crimes keep happening!

101
00:05:23,823 --> 00:05:24,699
[rattling]

102
00:05:24,782 --> 00:05:26,034
That's why you!

103
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:29,912
President Mendoza, step down!

104
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:32,957
After all, you are not doing anything

105
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:35,793
to resolve the country's problems!

106
00:05:42,467 --> 00:05:45,553
[pensive music playing]

107
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:04,113
Doctor…

108
00:06:05,698 --> 00:06:08,201
I'm sorry, but are you alright?

109
00:06:10,995 --> 00:06:13,956
I've noticed in the ER…

110
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:16,334
that you seem to be lost in thought.

111
00:06:20,713 --> 00:06:25,301
I was thinking…
about Allan's missing bandage.

112
00:06:27,386 --> 00:06:29,347
[pensive music continues]

113
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:39,398
His bloody bandage…

114
00:06:41,859 --> 00:06:45,321
T-The bloody bandage…

115
00:06:45,404 --> 00:06:46,739
of Major Espina?

116
00:06:49,033 --> 00:06:51,035
[Teresa sighs]

117
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:55,123
I wanted…

118
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:58,835
to get its DNA tested.

119
00:06:59,627 --> 00:07:01,504
I have a strong feeling…

120
00:07:02,088 --> 00:07:04,257
that Allan might be Gabriel.

121
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:07,927
[Datu Rahman]
<i>I tried to stop the explosion.</i>

122
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:10,138
But I failed.

123
00:07:12,181 --> 00:07:13,808
The truth is…

124
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:20,481
that's how I found your brother, Jalil.

125
00:07:22,358 --> 00:07:25,945
It has been almost 30 years, Jamilah.

126
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:29,991
But we only now found out

127
00:07:30,074 --> 00:07:31,868
what really happened on the ship.

128
00:07:35,246 --> 00:07:37,957
Even Marcus is very frustrated.

129
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:40,126
He's very disappointed because…

130
00:07:40,668 --> 00:07:44,755
Sir Mustapha is the only one
who knows the truth

131
00:07:44,839 --> 00:07:46,591
about what really happened to that ship,

132
00:07:46,674 --> 00:07:49,093
about what really happened to Gabriel.

133
00:07:49,677 --> 00:07:51,095
But…

134
00:07:51,971 --> 00:07:53,431
He's dead.

135
00:07:54,974 --> 00:07:56,476
They killed him.

136
00:07:57,351 --> 00:07:59,562
[pensive music continues]

137
00:08:01,105 --> 00:08:03,441
[Jamilah breathing shakily]

138
00:08:05,151 --> 00:08:07,695
What is your husband's name?

139
00:08:07,778 --> 00:08:09,906
[pensive music continues]

140
00:08:16,204 --> 00:08:18,039
Why do you ask?

141
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:24,128
Uh, j-just because.

142
00:08:24,712 --> 00:08:27,840
I was thinking he died on the ship, too.

143
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:30,843
You never mentioned anything.

144
00:08:36,265 --> 00:08:37,308
[Teresa exhaling]

145
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:39,227
Victor.

146
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:42,563
His name is Victor.

147
00:08:42,647 --> 00:08:45,608
But even before the ship sank…

148
00:08:46,651 --> 00:08:48,444
He had already left us.

149
00:08:50,279 --> 00:08:51,489
I never saw him again.

150
00:08:52,073 --> 00:08:53,491
[Jamilah gasps shakily]

151
00:08:54,450 --> 00:08:56,744
He was the son of my friend Victor.

152
00:08:57,870 --> 00:09:02,250
He and I tried to stop
the ship from exploding.

153
00:09:02,959 --> 00:09:04,502
Because…

154
00:09:04,585 --> 00:09:07,880
his family was aboard.

155
00:09:08,673 --> 00:09:10,550
[Jamilah stammers]

156
00:09:11,175 --> 00:09:12,468
[Jamilah] <i>It's Jalil.</i>

157
00:09:13,928 --> 00:09:16,806
<i>He is Doctor Teresa's son, Gabriel.</i>

158
00:09:17,598 --> 00:09:18,599
[Jamilah breathes shakily]

159
00:09:20,476 --> 00:09:22,395
Are you alright, Jamilah?

160
00:09:22,478 --> 00:09:25,356
[dramatic music playing]

161
00:09:31,112 --> 00:09:31,988
[Jamilah gulps]

162
00:09:32,655 --> 00:09:34,031
I'm alright, Doctor Teresa.

163
00:09:34,865 --> 00:09:38,327
I just need to do something outside.

164
00:09:39,161 --> 00:09:42,206
[somber music playing]

165
00:09:58,014 --> 00:10:01,309
[Jamilah] <i>Please forgive me,</i>
<i>Doctor Teresa and Jalil.</i>

166
00:10:01,392 --> 00:10:03,728
<i>I don't want to deny you the opportunity</i>

167
00:10:03,811 --> 00:10:06,606
<i>to get to know each other</i>
<i>as mother and son.</i>

168
00:10:09,984 --> 00:10:12,236
<i>But Jalil's mission is dangerous.</i>

169
00:10:13,237 --> 00:10:16,324
<i>And I have to protect his identity.</i>

170
00:10:16,907 --> 00:10:18,701
[somber music continues]

171
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:29,420
[suspenseful music playing]

172
00:10:32,298 --> 00:10:33,924
[door creaks open]

173
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:40,616
- Fernando.
- [Fernando] General.

174
00:11:59,385 --> 00:12:01,804
You already know who to deliver these to.

175
00:12:01,887 --> 00:12:03,139
Yes, General.

176
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:07,059
To Senator Acopio, Congressman Tanjoco,

177
00:12:07,143 --> 00:12:09,645
one to General Biglang-Awa…

178
00:12:09,728 --> 00:12:11,814
And, lastly, to Secretary Vergara.

179
00:12:38,340 --> 00:12:39,592
[Madrigal] Alright,
start delivering those.

180
00:12:51,103 --> 00:12:52,313
[car engine revs]

181
00:12:52,396 --> 00:12:54,690
[suspenseful music continues]

182
00:13:15,377 --> 00:13:17,379
[dog barking]

183
00:13:17,922 --> 00:13:19,173
Shh!

184
00:13:35,523 --> 00:13:36,774
[dog barking]

185
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:40,277
[dog barking]

186
00:13:40,861 --> 00:13:42,321
[dog barking in distance]

187
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:44,448
[dog barking]

188
00:13:45,574 --> 00:13:47,785
[dog barking in distance]

189
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,001
Cuchy?

190
00:13:58,462 --> 00:14:00,047
Is there anyone there?

191
00:14:00,130 --> 00:14:01,507
[dog barking]

192
00:14:01,590 --> 00:14:03,133
Cuchy?

193
00:14:07,596 --> 00:14:08,597
Cuchy?

194
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,866
[dog panting, whimpers]

195
00:15:00,774 --> 00:15:02,026
[dog panting]

196
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:04,820
[dog barking, whimpers]

197
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:07,072
What's going on, huh?

198
00:15:08,407 --> 00:15:11,160
Who went inside? Who?

199
00:15:12,536 --> 00:15:14,455
Did you see who?

200
00:15:14,538 --> 00:15:15,873
Did you?

201
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:19,251
I'll get him.

202
00:15:20,669 --> 00:15:21,962
Whoever that is.

203
00:15:22,588 --> 00:15:23,672
[chuckles sarcastically]

204
00:15:24,465 --> 00:15:25,674
Don't worry.

205
00:15:26,383 --> 00:15:29,178
I'll catch that bastard.

206
00:15:29,261 --> 00:15:33,015
He thinks he can get away with it, Cuchy?

207
00:15:33,098 --> 00:15:34,516
He won't.

208
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,644
He won't get away with this.

209
00:15:36,727 --> 00:15:39,146
[smooches]

210
00:15:39,229 --> 00:15:43,150
[chuckles]

211
00:15:47,488 --> 00:15:50,240
[tense music playing]

212
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:10,344
- [blows, kicks landing]
- [grunts] Argh!

213
00:16:17,476 --> 00:16:19,269
- [blows, kicks landing]
- [grunts] Argh!

214
00:16:22,272 --> 00:16:24,274
Hello, Reyes?

215
00:16:24,358 --> 00:16:26,568
Report status, Reyes. Hello?

216
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:28,278
- [blows, kicks landing]
- [grunts] Argh!

217
00:16:33,951 --> 00:16:34,952
Reyes!

218
00:16:36,328 --> 00:16:38,497
- [groans] Argh!
- [plastic rustling]

219
00:16:49,174 --> 00:16:50,342
- [stabs]
- [grunts] Argh!

220
00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:04,648
What's happening to you, Reyes?!

221
00:17:04,732 --> 00:17:07,526
[tense music continues]

222
00:17:09,111 --> 00:17:10,863
[grunts]

223
00:17:10,946 --> 00:17:12,448
[pensive music playing]

224
00:17:14,950 --> 00:17:16,076
Reyes?

225
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:28,213
[pensive music continues]

226
00:17:40,517 --> 00:17:41,769
Reyes?

227
00:17:41,852 --> 00:17:42,978
Reyes?!

228
00:17:43,062 --> 00:17:44,313
Answer me!

229
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:45,522
Reyes!

230
00:17:51,528 --> 00:17:52,738
[car door closes]

231
00:17:54,948 --> 00:17:57,117
[suspenseful music continues]

232
00:18:27,648 --> 00:18:28,732
Reyes?

233
00:18:30,818 --> 00:18:31,860
Reyes!

234
00:18:33,862 --> 00:18:34,905
Reyes!

235
00:18:42,788 --> 00:18:43,956
Goddamnit!

236
00:18:49,837 --> 00:18:52,422
[door closes]

237
00:19:19,032 --> 00:19:20,367
Where did you go?

238
00:19:21,243 --> 00:19:23,579
[suspenseful music continues]

239
00:19:29,376 --> 00:19:32,045
- [blow lands]
- [grunts] Argh!

240
00:19:37,968 --> 00:19:40,596
I was just surprised
to see that he was following me.

241
00:19:41,471 --> 00:19:43,807
General Carillo was right.

242
00:19:44,850 --> 00:19:46,810
He definitely knows something about us.

243
00:19:47,811 --> 00:19:50,898
We really need to find out what that is.

244
00:19:53,775 --> 00:19:55,277
[in distorted voice] <i>Hey, Reyes.</i>

245
00:19:56,320 --> 00:19:57,821
<i>What did Mustapha tell you?</i>

246
00:19:58,572 --> 00:20:00,407
Tell me everything you know.

247
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:04,494
I have nothing to say to you, bastard!

248
00:20:05,329 --> 00:20:07,623
Let me go and fight me fairly!

249
00:20:07,706 --> 00:20:09,208
[man] You think you're tough, huh?

250
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:10,876
Let's see how long you'll last!

251
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:14,713
- [grunts] Argh!
- [yells] Ahh!

252
00:20:14,796 --> 00:20:17,424
[groans] <i>Argh!</i>

253
00:20:25,807 --> 00:20:28,977
Reyes has been following General Madrigal,

254
00:20:29,061 --> 00:20:32,064
who was sending suitcases of money

255
00:20:32,147 --> 00:20:33,232
before he disappeared!

256
00:20:33,815 --> 00:20:35,400
What happened to him?

257
00:20:35,484 --> 00:20:37,819
- Is he dead?
- [Jalil] No, no, no.

258
00:20:37,903 --> 00:20:39,238
If they wanted to kill Reyes,

259
00:20:39,321 --> 00:20:41,657
they should have done it right there.

260
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:42,574
[Azuelo] That's right!

261
00:20:42,658 --> 00:20:44,618
They didn't kill Reyes.

262
00:20:45,494 --> 00:20:47,037
But they kidnapped him!

263
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:49,039
What would they gain by kidnapping him?

264
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:54,378
They're trying to find out what he knows.

265
00:20:55,671 --> 00:20:58,173
[suspenseful music continues]

266
00:21:00,175 --> 00:21:01,343
[grunts] Argh!

267
00:21:09,935 --> 00:21:11,019
[groans]

268
00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:13,146
[man] This is one tough bastard.

269
00:21:13,730 --> 00:21:15,774
He passed out because it was too much.

270
00:21:16,608 --> 00:21:18,485
But he still won't say a word.

271
00:21:18,568 --> 00:21:22,614
[cellphone ringing]

272
00:21:26,827 --> 00:21:28,203
Solares.

273
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:29,955
[Solares] <i>He's a tough one.</i>

274
00:21:30,956 --> 00:21:33,000
He refuses to speak no matter what we do.

275
00:21:33,709 --> 00:21:34,918
[chuckles]

276
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:37,879
Just keep going.

277
00:21:38,714 --> 00:21:40,382
He'll give in eventually.

278
00:21:40,465 --> 00:21:41,675
[chuckles]

279
00:21:41,758 --> 00:21:47,514
Everyone has a breaking point.

280
00:21:48,098 --> 00:21:49,016
[chuckles]

281
00:21:51,727 --> 00:21:53,020
Yes, General.

282
00:21:53,103 --> 00:21:55,439
[suspenseful music continues]

283
00:22:05,407 --> 00:22:08,327
- [Teresa sighs]
- [morose music playing]

284
00:22:09,953 --> 00:22:11,580
I wonder where Marcus is.

285
00:22:12,331 --> 00:22:13,915
It's already dawn.

286
00:22:13,999 --> 00:22:15,625
I wonder where that kid is.

287
00:22:18,754 --> 00:22:20,339
[exhales sharply]

288
00:22:23,633 --> 00:22:25,469
[voice prompt]
<i>The subscriber cannot be reached.</i>

289
00:22:25,552 --> 00:22:27,179
<i>Please try again later.</i>

290
00:22:32,893 --> 00:22:34,186
[sniffles]

291
00:22:34,770 --> 00:22:35,896
[exhales sharply]

292
00:22:35,979 --> 00:22:37,773
[knocking on door]

293
00:22:38,315 --> 00:22:39,983
Marcus? Is that you?

294
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:41,860
Did you leave your key?

295
00:22:43,737 --> 00:22:46,281
- Oh, Allan.
- Doctor.

296
00:22:47,365 --> 00:22:50,243
Yes? Come in. Come in.

297
00:22:55,624 --> 00:22:56,875
Allan, what…

298
00:22:56,958 --> 00:23:00,087
What are you doing here?
Aren't you with Marcus?

299
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:03,673
[tense music playing]

300
00:23:03,757 --> 00:23:05,926
Allan, what's going on?

301
00:23:10,305 --> 00:23:11,848
[breathes deeply]

302
00:23:12,599 --> 00:23:15,685
It's… uh… It's about Marcus.

303
00:23:21,108 --> 00:23:23,693
What happened to my son?

304
00:23:24,611 --> 00:23:26,113
[breathes deeply]

305
00:23:26,196 --> 00:23:28,573
Doc, Marcus got kidnapped.

306
00:23:30,367 --> 00:23:32,244
I want to be the one to tell you myself

307
00:23:32,327 --> 00:23:33,662
before you hear it from someone else.

308
00:23:33,745 --> 00:23:35,580
Before it spreads in the news.

309
00:23:35,664 --> 00:23:36,832
[sobs]

310
00:23:39,918 --> 00:23:42,963
- [crying] Oh my God, my son.
- Doc, please.

311
00:23:43,046 --> 00:23:45,340
[sobs]

312
00:23:45,423 --> 00:23:46,758
Doc, don't worry.

313
00:23:46,842 --> 00:23:48,301
[exhales sharply]

314
00:23:49,010 --> 00:23:51,012
You won't lose another child.

315
00:23:52,848 --> 00:23:54,683
I'm going to look for Marcus.

316
00:23:54,766 --> 00:23:56,768
He'll return home to you safely.

317
00:23:58,812 --> 00:24:00,939
I'll do anything to find him.

318
00:24:01,022 --> 00:24:02,315
[crying]

319
00:24:02,399 --> 00:24:03,859
[sobs]

320
00:24:06,153 --> 00:24:07,320
I…

321
00:24:08,071 --> 00:24:09,865
I found this where he was kidnapped.

322
00:24:09,948 --> 00:24:11,950
[breathing heavily]

323
00:24:12,033 --> 00:24:15,078
[tense music continues]

324
00:24:19,916 --> 00:24:22,127
No, you need to give that back to him

325
00:24:22,210 --> 00:24:24,087
as soon as you find him.

326
00:24:25,046 --> 00:24:27,215
[somber music playing]

327
00:24:31,970 --> 00:24:33,763
[sniffles]

328
00:24:35,098 --> 00:24:36,433
I need to go.

329
00:24:37,100 --> 00:24:40,061
I promise I'll give this back to Marcus.

330
00:24:41,354 --> 00:24:42,772
I'll find your son.

331
00:24:45,734 --> 00:24:46,902
Thank you…

332
00:24:47,569 --> 00:24:48,737
son.

333
00:24:50,530 --> 00:24:53,158
[somber music continues]

334
00:25:24,272 --> 00:25:25,649
Sir Marcus was kidnapped?

335
00:25:26,233 --> 00:25:28,568
[Jalil] <i>We'll find Reyes. We'll find him.</i>

336
00:25:28,652 --> 00:25:30,362
You seem happy
about what happened to Reyes.

337
00:25:30,445 --> 00:25:33,573
Nothing bad will happen to him…
because he wasn't a nice guy.

338
00:25:33,657 --> 00:25:35,867
- [crying]
- <i>I'll find Marcus.</i>

339
00:25:35,951 --> 00:25:38,536
You won't lose another child.

340
00:25:38,620 --> 00:25:41,831
What do you know?
What did Mustapha tell you?

341
00:25:42,666 --> 00:25:46,169
Come out. Show yourself, you bastard!

342
00:25:46,253 --> 00:25:48,171
- [electricity buzzes]
- [screams] <i>Aah!</i>

343
00:25:49,506 --> 00:25:51,591
- [tires screeching]
- [man] <i>We're being ambushed!</i>

344
00:25:53,593 --> 00:25:55,679
<i>I'm afraid to face Jalil.</i>

345
00:25:55,762 --> 00:25:57,597
But it is his right to know the truth.

346
00:25:57,681 --> 00:26:00,558
I'm sure he'll understand why you did it.

347
00:26:00,642 --> 00:26:03,395
This is not an easy decision to make.

348
00:26:03,478 --> 00:26:05,647
My new Chief of Staff…

349
00:26:05,730 --> 00:26:09,859
[Jamilah] <i>I feel guilty</i>
<i>because I can't tell Jalil the truth.</i>

350
00:26:09,943 --> 00:26:13,280
<i>That the person in danger…</i>
<i>is his own brother.</i>

351
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:14,906
We're in position.

352
00:26:14,990 --> 00:26:16,116
[Jalil] <i>I'm ready to take the risk.</i>

353
00:26:16,199 --> 00:26:19,119
[man]
<i>It looks like Reyes won't say a word.</i>
